<HEADLINE> Overseas Investors Looking At Three Gorges Area (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- A large commercial mission from
the Paris Chamber of Industry and Commerce today left Beijing for
the Three Gorges Reservoir Area to sign a letter of intent for a
series of projects.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of Germany's Song International Trade Company
Ltd. arrived in Beijing several days ago after an inspection tour
of the Three Gorges Reservoir Area and signed an agreement with
China in preparation for funding building materials businesses and
small hydro-electric power stations that will involve 500 million
yuan in investment.
</P>
<P>
The German company has won a bid on another water control
project being built at Xiaolangdi on the Yellow River in Henan
Province.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, an official with the State Council
Three Gorges Project Construction Committee's Bureau of
Resettlement and Development said that, in the past year, large
companies and financial organizations from Germany, France,
Britain, and other countries have shown interest in investing in
infrastructure projects in the Three Gorges area.
</P>
<P>
The Resettlement and Development Bureau has been increasing
efforts to publicize the Three Gorges resettlement principle of
development projects with the idea of getting more funds from
overseas.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971014.0002 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas Investors Looking at Three Gorges Area (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Three Gorges area begins in the Chongqing municipality and
ends at Yichang in Hubei province. The Three Gorges Project has
attracted worldwide attention partly because of the large number
of residents to be relocated.
</P>
<P>
To make a success of the resettlement work, the Chinese
government worked out policies to encourage people overseas to
invest in the Three Gorges Reservoir area. The State Council Three
Gorges Construction Committee held a special meeting in Beijing
last December to explain resettlement and economic development
there.
</P>
<P>
This year, two economic and technological co-operation tours
have been organized by the committee to brief foreigners on the
project, and an American company is preparing a site for growing
improved varieties of oranges, providing technical training, and
processing fruit juice in Chongqing with an 80 million U.S.-dollar
investment.
</P>
<P>
The Italian government is talking of a sewage treatment project
in Dazu on the upper reaches of the reservoir with 3.9 million
U.S. dollars in loans.
</P>
<P>
A number of infrastructure projects like an airport in Yichang,
an expressway from Wuhan to Yichang, and a number of small
hydro-electric and thermal power stations have been completed, and
automatic switchboards and direct domestic and international
dialing systems have been put into service in 21 counties and
cities of the Three Gorges Reservoir area.
</P>
<P>
Governments in the reservoir area have also simplified approval
procedures of foreign-funded projects, and have worked out
preferential policies to encourage foreign investment. A group of
economic and technological development zones have also been
established in the region.
</P>
<P>
The advantageous investment conditions are attracting more
overseas companies. New Zealand's MIL Company is considering
investing in three expressways there, and another New Zealand
company is showing an interest in the second phase project of the
Yichang Thermal Power Plant and Jiangkou Hydropower Station in
Chongqing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
