<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-13 15:58 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 11 Killed by Suspected Militants in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Unidentified gunmen today
attacked Egypt's policemen in patrols in southern Egypt, killing
eight policemen and three civilians, the Middle East News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The assailants opened fire on policemen in two separate attacks
at Mawawi and Abu Korkas in Minya, about 230 kilometers south of
Cairo, MENA quoted a source of the Interior Ministry as saying.
</P>
<P>
The gunmen escaped and there is no immediate claim of
responsibility for the attack, which is the bloodiest against the
security forces this year.
</P>
<P>
Investigations into the killings are under way. Minya, the
Upper Egyptian governorate, is notorious for frequent terrorism in
the past five years,
</P>
<P>
In the latest terrorist attack in Minya, suspected Muslim
militants beheaded a policeman and shot dead a farmer in two
separate attacks on September 30.
</P>
<P>
The latest deaths brought to 1,255 the number of people killed
by Muslim extremists since they launched an anti-government campaign
in March 1992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
