<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1530 GMT, October 13 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL -- The South Korean Defense Ministry announced today that
it had decided to purchase French-made Mistral portable missiles
rather than U.S. Stinger or British Starburst missiles.
</P>
<P>
About 1,000 Mistral systems, valued at 250 billion won (275
million U.S. dollars), will be imported between 1998-1999 to
enhance the army's local air defense capabilities, the ministry
said. (SKorea-France-Arms)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
STOCKHOLM -- Sweden's third largest bank, Nordbanken, and
Finland's main bank, Merita Bank, announced their merger Monday.
</P>
<P>
The merger creates the Nordic region's largest banking group,
which is worth more than 10 billion
U.S. dollars. (Sweden-Bank-Merger)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SEOUL -- South Korean President Kim Young-sam's second son, Kim
Hyun-chul, was sentenced to three-year imprisonment today by the
Seoul District Court for charges of tax evasion and taking bribes.
</P>
<P>
The junior Kim was also ordered to pay a fine of 1.44 billion
won (about 1.6 million U.S. dollars) for tax evasion and an
additional penalty of 524.2 million won (about 582,000
U.S. dollars) for taking bribes from businessmen.
</P>
<P>
Kim, 38, was arrested on May 17 and indicted on June 5, charged
with influence-peddling and tax evasion. (SKorea-President's
son-Trial)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CARACAS -- U.S. President Bill Clinton arrived here Monday to
start his first South America trip, aiming to strengthen trade
with that part of America.
</P>
<P>
Clinton chose October 12, the Columbus Day, as the day to start
his tour. The day is a common holiday celebrated in most of the
North and South American countries for the discovery of Columbus
some 500 years ago. (Venezuela-Clinton-Visit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BUCHAREST -- North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO)
Secretary General Javier Solana said today the expansion of the
military alliance would not be limited simply by geography.
</P>
<P>
At a plenary session of the North Atlantic Assembly (NAA),
Solana said that enlargement would be defined by common values,
not merely by geographical division.
</P>
<P>
He said that NATO's expansion membership would include all
those qualified, including Russia, if it intended to apply for
entry into the NATO. (NATO-Expansion-Solana)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LEIPZIG -- German Chancellor Helmut Kohl launched his campaign
today to seek an unprecedented fifth term in next year's general
elections.
</P>
<P>
The announcement came after a strong appeal for solidarity
within his own party and sharp criticism of the main opposition
Social Democratic Party (SPD).
</P>
<P>
Addressing the national congress of his ruling Christian
Democratic Union Party in the eastern city of Leipzig, Kohl said
the election campaign for the 1998 general elections had already
begun. (Germany-Reelection Campaign) 
</P>
</TEXT>
