<HEADLINE> Angola to Fight Back Congo (B) Military Assaults </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
LUANDA, October 13 (Xinhua) --The Angolan Defense Ministry
said in a communique that Angola armed forces would take "proper
actions" against assualts from the Republic of Congo, Angolan
News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The communique, issued Sunday, said that the land and air
territory in Cabinda Province in northern Angola has been
violated quite several times by the armed forces from the
Republic of Congo since armed conflicts erupted in the country.
</P>
<P>
The violations against the Angolan province have escalated
into "rampant attacks" against civiliants#,police and the armed
forces stationed on the border, the communique said.
</P>
<P>
With the intensifying of the attacks, the communique said,
Angola has suffered personnel and material losses, so proper
steps will be taken to fight back attacks from Congo. 
</P>
