<HEADLINE> Chinese Flight Demonstration Praised in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The Aviation Industry of China
(AVIC) and China National Aero-Technology Import and Export
Corporation (CATIC) conducted flight demonstration here today and
won admiration from Zimbabwean air force officers and foreign
military attaches in Harare.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft which gave flight demonstration are k-8 jet
trainer and y7-100 commuter airliner and y7h-500 cargo aircraft.
</P>
<P>
AVIC's Deputy General Manager Wang Ang said that k-8 is a
military jet trainer co-developed by CATIC, China Nanchang
Aircraft Manufacturing Company and Pakistan air force. With
reliable performance and easy maintenance requirements, six k-8s
have successfully passed a two-year evaluation carried out by
Pakistan air force. They are now serving in the Pakistan air
force.
</P>
<P>
The y-7 aircraft family are famous for their convenient usage,
strong structure and easy maintenance. They are manufactured by
China Xian Aircraft Manufacturing Company. Up to August, 1997,
118 various versions of y-7 aircraft family have been provided to
customers worldwide.
</P>
<P>
The pilots of k-8 make the brilliant demonstrations in low
speed, roll, loop. Zimbabwe's Air Force Commander Perence Shiri
commended their superb skill.
</P>
<P>
This flight demonstration will also be held in Zambia, Kenya
and Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
Wang Ang expressed his hope that the flight demonstration will
promote the aero-technology cooperation between the African
countries and China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
