<HEADLINE> U.S. Satisfied With Angolan Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, October 13 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton's
special envoy Paul Hare said here today that the U.S. government
is satisfied with the recent progress in Angola's peace process.
</P>
<P>
The visiting U.S. envoy made the remark after he met with UN
special envoy Blondin Beye, saying that his government is content
with the facts that progress has been made in re-establishing
central government institutions and local government organs in
some of the strategic areas controlled by the National Union for
Total Independence of Angola (UNITA).
</P>
