<HEADLINE> Annan Appoints Mr. Sevan the Executive Director of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 13 (Xinhua) -- UN Secretary-General
Kofi Annan has decided today to appoint Benon V. sevan, a national
of Cyprus as the Executive Director of the Office of the Iraq
Program, effective October 15, 1997, said a statement issued
today by the spokesman's office.
</P>
<P>
Since July 1994, Mr. Sevan has been serving as the Assistant
Secretary-General for Conference and support Services and United
Nations Security Council Coordinator, and will continue to carry
out the latter function.
</P>
<P>
From August 1992 to March 1994, Sevan served as Assistant
Secretary-General in the Department of Political Affairs, with
particular responsibility for General Assembly and Security
Council Affairs.
</P>
<P>
Mr. Seven, born in 1937, is a graduate of the Melkonian
Educational Institute in Cyprus. He obtained a Bachelor Arts
degree in History and Philosophy from Columbia College, Columbia
University, New York. He also has a graduate degree from the
School of International and Public Affairs of Columbia University.
</P>
