<HEADLINE> Earthquake Shocks Athens, Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, October 13 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.5 on
the richter scale shocked the Greek capital this afternoon, but no
damages have been reported.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake occurred at 4:40 p.m. local time with the
epicenter being in the seabed 250 kilometers southwest of Athens,
about 100 kilometers south of Kalamata in southern Pelopponese.
the Athens Seismological Institute and the Geophysics Laboratory
of the Aristotelian University of Thessaloniki said today.
</P>
<P>
Seismologists advised local residents to evacuate their older
homes for the next 48 hours as a precaution because they were not
sure whether today's quake was the precursor to a stronger one.
</P>
<P>
Today's quake came nearly 11 years after the quake in Kalamata,
which killed 20 people and injured more than 30. 
</P>
</TEXT>
