<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The visiting Swedish Foreign
Minister Lena Hjelm-Wallen said here today that all parties in the
region should try to save the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
In her statements to newsmen after having talks with her Syrian
counterpart Farouk Sharaa, She said that Syria is an important
country in the peace process, but the process itself has been
stalled.
</P>
<P>
"We ought to be constructive and should endeavor to do more,"
she said, expressing hope that all parties in the region would try
to make further effort to save the peace process.
</P>
<P>
The Swedish Minister said, "we have discussed the relationship
between Sweden and Syria and ways and means of promoting bilateral
ties. Likewise, we exchanged views about the situation in the
Middle East and the prospects of putting the peace process back on
track."
</P>
<P>
On the role of Sweden in salvaging the peace process, she said
that being a member of the European Union and the U.N. Security
Council, Sweden is seeking more facts about the situation and
developments in the region. This will help Sweden do something
through the U.N. and the EU, she said, adding that she wishes the
EU will have greater presence in seeking for a resolution of this
conflict.
</P>
<P>
The Swedish Minister arrived in Damascus last evening on a
three-day official visit to Syria. 
</P>
