<HEADLINE> Mozambique Launches Vote Education Drive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, October (Xinhua) -- Mozambique launched a national
education campaign to mobilize the broad masses to register for
the vote scheduled from 10 to 30 of October.
</P>
<P>
Marceliono Silva, director of the office of the Secretariat
of the Election Technology Administration, said that the
campaign will take 45 days.
</P>
<P>
Silva said that TV stations, newspapers and radio stations
and helicopter would be used in the campaign, with 1,770
educators to be sent to factories, schools, markets and other
public places.
</P>
<P>
Organizers also use 17 automobiles and some sound equipment
for the campaign, Silva said, adding that they were ready for
the November campaign.
</P>
<P>
The voters' registration will cost 11.5 million U.S.
Dollars, with 7.8 million voters in the 17 million people.
</P>
<P>
The first voters' registration in the country was in 1994
when Mozambique had a presidential and parliamentary election.
</P>
<P>
The first local election is expected to be held in April
next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
