<DOCNO> XIE19971014.0048 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Calls on to Establish True Global Partnership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 13 (xinhua) -- It is essential to
establish a true global partnership on the principles of mutual
benefits and common but differentiated responsibilities so as to
promote common prosperity and development of developing countries
and other countries in the world, Qin Huasun, Chinese Permanent
Representative to the United Nations stressed here today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the general debate of the Second Committee at the
fifty-second session of the General Assembly, Ambassador Qin said
a total of 1.3 billion people in developing countries are yet to
be free from poverty.
</P>
<P>
Qin said the unfavorable external environment is still
hampering the efforts of developing countries for economic and
social development: there have been frequent tendencies of trade
protectionism and unilateralism by developed countries; heavy debt
burden has slowed the development pace of the developing
countries; Official Development Aid has dropped to a new all-time
low; the gap between the developed and the developing countries is
further widening; and in the tide of the globalization, the least
developed countries are in a real danger of being marginalized,
while developing countries with fairly good development are
frequently confronted with new challenges and adversities.
</P>
<P>
Qin said in the United Nations, the tendency of paying
inadequate attention to development issues has yet to be
corrected, development resources have continued to decrease, and
the institutions involved in economic development activities have
suffered further weakening.
</P>
<P>
Qin said though an Agenda for Development has been adopted and
the Special Session for the Comprehensive Review of the Outcome of
the Conference on environment and Development had been convened,
the consensus reached by the international community at a series
of major international conference on strengthening international
development cooperation remains, to a large extent, on paper.
</P>
<P>
Qin said when economic inter-relations and interdependence
among states are ever deepening, it is impossible for the
prosperity and affluence of a few countries to be built on the
continuous poverty and backwardness of a majority of countries.
Developing countries need developed countries, developed countries
also need developing countries. Developing countries are
indispensable as markets for products and capital from the
developed countries, and are sources for the raw materials
developed countries require.
</P>
<P>
Qin stressed it is essential to observe the principles of
equality and mutual benefits, to adhere to the correct orientation
of international development cooperation, to constantly revise the
content of international development cooperation in light of the
new features in today's world economy and new needs arising
therefrom, and to strengthen UN's role in promoting international
development cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
