<DOCNO> XIE19971014.0049 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qin Huasun on Reform of the United Nations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The strengthening of
UN's role in promoting international development cooperation is
closely linked to the current UN reform process, Qin Huasun,
Chinese Permanent Representative to the United Nations said here
today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the general debate of the Economic and Financial
Committee at the fifty-second session of the General Assembly, Qin
said reform of the Organization must grasp the theme of the times
and bring the question of development back to the center of the UN
agenda together with the question of peace.
</P>
<P>
Qin said reform should follow a democratic principle. The
reform of the UN is a matter for the entire membership. questions
relating to the reform of inter-governmental machinery, in
particularly, should be subject to in-depth discussions by the
member states and acted upon the basis of general consensus.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador said reform measures should focus on the
strengthening out relations, improving efficiency in the UN
system, which demanded a prompt solution.
</P>
<P>
he said effective settlement of serious inadequacy of
development resources is an important component of the UN reform,
particularly reform in the economic and financial field. It is
necessary to take the question of resources into overall
consideration as part of reform so as to ensure a reliable and
stable basis for development resources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
