<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Otis Confident in China Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Otis, the world's largest
elevator manufacturer, is expanding its Chinese market, which it
believes has a great need for its products.
</P>
<P>
"China is a very important market to Otis as it is the fastest
growing elevator market in the world," said Stephen Page,
president and chief executive officer of Otis Elevator.
</P>
<P>
"An estimated 200,000 elevators are expected to be needed in
China over the next five years," he said during a recent interview
with Chinese reporters. He said that China is now second only to
Japan as the largest market for new equipment units.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Otis sold about 5,000 units in China, more than 20
percent of its worldwide yearly average of 42,000 units.
</P>
<P>
Otis Elevator's long history in China began in the 1900s with
the installation of two elevators in Shanghai's Peace Hotel by the
Huangpu River in 1907. But during the several decades afterwards,
Otis was unable to make much expansion on the China market.
</P>
<P>
Otis took the opportunities brought by China's economic reforms
and opening-up policies, and set up its first manufacturing joint
venture in China at Tianjin in 1984. The Tianjin venture
manufactures a full range of products, Page said. In the following
years, Otis has other manufacturing joint ventures in Guangzhou
and Hangzhou, and sales and service joint ventures in Beijing and
Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
On September 8, Otis announced the formation of Otis China
Limited, a joint venture holding company that will manage its
five operations in China. Its partners are CITIC Development
Company Ltd. and Tianjin Tai Kang Industrial and Commercial Co.
</P>
<P>
"The linkage of our various operations around China will help
us achieve synergy in managing our marketing, manufacturing and
product development resources," he said. "It will also enhance our
abilities to provide better services to our customers throughout
China." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
