<HEADLINE> Iran Tests Unmanned Plane Successfully </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Iran announced here today
that an unmanned plane built by Iran itself had a successful
test flight in the Persian Gulf today.
</P>
<P>
The official news agency IRNA reported that "Stealth", the
domestically built unmanned plane, was test flown in the
Persian Gulf Tuesday as part of the war games being conducted
by Iranian navy.
</P>
<P>
Ashkbus Danekar, commander of Khatam al-Anbia Headquarters, was
 quoted as saying that the unmanned plane successfully carried
out its mission at the third stage of the Victory-8 military
exercise in the Gulf.
</P>
<P>
He said the reconnaissance aircraft which cannot be detected
on radar screen has served to complete the offensive and
defensive capability of the Iranian navy.
</P>
<P>
During its surveillance mission, the plane is also capable
of detecting other flying unmanned aircraft within its range,
taking photos and transmitting information about their place,
movement and speed, the official said.
</P>
<P>
According to another report, a new training warplane "Dorna"
which has been manufactured by Iran's Air Force experts will
conduct its first test flight soon.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the aircraft is made of composite
material and is unique in its kind. 
</P>
</TEXT>
