<HEADLINE> Ministerial Panel At World Petroleum Congress  (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The 15th World Petroleum
Congress, which opened Sunday in Beijing, had a ministerial panel
today for representatives of Algeria, the U.S., India, Pakistan,
Cuba, Brazil, Nigeria, Canada, Iran, Mozambique, and Angola.
</P>
<P>
Minister for Petroleum and Natural Gas of India Janeshwar
Mishra called petroleum and gas "one of the most important
energies in the world", and said that development and co-operation
are the topic of energy and oil industries of all countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that his country has taken steps and developed new
policy initiatives like the New Exploration Licensing Policy that
are intended to give a major boost to exploration and production
activity by involving the private sector and providing open access
to exploration.
</P>
<P>
India has also been actively exploring production opportunities
abroad, the minister said, and the Middle East, the former Soviet
Union, Africa, and Southeast Asia have been areas of key interest
and focus.
</P>
<P>
About 120 to 150 billion US dollars in investment will be
needed to develop India's oil industry over the next 15 years, he
said.
</P>
