<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qiao Shi Visits International Petroleum Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of the
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, visited the
International Petroleum and Petrochemical Exhibition '97 in
Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
Accompanied by executives from major enterprises of the
country's oil, gas and petrochemical industries, Qiao visited the
pavilions exhibiting China's major oil-fields, gas-fileds and the
petrochemical industry.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said that China's petroleum industry has achieved notable
progress since the country launched its reform and opening drive
in 1979. China has made achievements in off-shore oil prospecting
and exploration in recent years, he noted.
</P>
<P>
He praised the Daqing Oilfield for its outstanding
contributions to the country in the past decades, expressing the
hope that Daqing would make still greater achievements through
technological progress.
</P>
<P>
China is relatively deficient in petroleum resources and should
further its cooperation with foreign countries in oil prospecting,
drilling, refining and research.
</P>
<P>
The leader praised the sponsors for holding such an exhibition,
saying that it could increase mutual understanding and exchanges
between China's oil industry and its foreign counterparts, and it
will also help boost the development of the country's oil
industry.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is held at the China International Exhibition
Center and attended by 400 companies from 24 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
All major Chinese oil companies are participating in
the exhibition, displaying their latest achievements in the
petroleum industry.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition covering 6,670 sq m., the largest ever in the
country's oil sector, is jointly sponsored by the China National
Petroleum Corp. (CNPC), China Petrochemical Corp. (Sinopec),
China National Offshore Oil Corp. (CNOOC), China National
Chemicals Import and Export Corp. (Sinochem) and China National
Star Petroleum Corp (CNSPC). 
