Palestinian imports and purchases collected by Israel on
behalf of the PNA, were frozen by Israel after the July 30 double
suicide bombing attack in Jewish west Jerusalem, in which 16
Israelis and the two suicide bombers were killed.
</P>
<P>
Due to the improvement of security cooperation between the two
sides, Israel has released about 40 percent of the funds to the
PNA, but the remaining 110 million dollars are still in the
Israeli hands, PNA finiance ministry said. 
