<HEADLINE> Olympic Shooting Champions Suffer Humiliating Defeats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Two Olympic champions in the
shooting competitions were toppled with poor performances, while
Chen Yan reapt her second swimming gold at the Eighth National
Games here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Yang Ling, winner of the men's 10m running target in the
Atlanta Olympic Games, finished in a disappointing 12th position
with 568 points in the preliminaries.
</P>
<P>
While Li Duihong who won the women's sport pistol in Atlanta,
ranked 15th with 378 points in the women's air pistol. Both were
eventually eliminated from the finals.
</P>
<P>
"We're not surprised for their losses, as many a sharpshooters
are of the same level in the country after the Atlanta Games,
especially those in the finals," said Zhang Heng, head coach of
the Chinese national shooting team.
</P>
<P>
Chen Yan, who broke the oldest swimming record in the women's
400m individual medley on Monday, showed her versatility on
Tuesday by touching home first in the 200-meter freestyle in
1:57.30.
</P>
<P>
"I'm glad to take my second gold medal from the pool," said the
16-year-old Chen, "I won it because I overcame fagigue in the last
50 meters."
</P>
<P>
Two Asian marks were broken in the pool as Wang Wei of Shanghai
clocked 1:08.26 in the women's 100-meter breaststroke and Xiong
Guoming clocked the best of 4:19.03 in the men's 400-meter
individual medley.
</P>
<P>
All the world records in the women's 54-kg and 59-kg classes
weightlifting competitions were broken by many a Chinese
strongwomen with huge margins, suggesting a juicy harvest for
China as the sport will make its debut in the 2000 Olympic Games
in Sydney.
</P>
<P>
The 18-year-old Chen Yanqing of Jiangsu province claimed the
59-kg title by lifting 112.5 kgs in snatch and 137.5 kgs in jerk
for a combined total of 250 kgs.
</P>
<P>
The previous marks were 100kgs in snatch, 125kg in jerk and
220kgs in the two-lift total.
</P>
<P>
Song Zhijuan, a 17-year-old strongwoman in the Liberation Army,
even snatched up 115 kgs to break the Chinese national record of
110.5 kgs set by Chen Xiaomin in the National Championships last
year.  And all the top four finishers bettered the three listed
marks.
</P>
<P>
Another teenager Yang Xia at the age of 19, also broke three
world records en route to taking the 54-kg category title with a
total of 232.5 kgs from 100 kgs in snatch and 132.5 kgs in jerk.
</P>
<P>
The previous marks were 93.5 kgs in snatch, 115.5 kgs in jerk
and 207.5 kgs in the two-lift total.
</P>
<P>
Yang Xia also broke the national jerk record of 130 kgs set up
by Chen Xiaomin at the previous National Games four years ago.
</P>
<P>
Nine of the 12 finalists surpassed all three world records in
the finals, while Long Yuling set up a new world record of 102.5
kgs in snatch. 
</P>
</TEXT>
