<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen Meets With Antigua and Barbuda Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen met with Prime Minister Lester Bird of
Antigua and Barbuda today.
</P>
<P>
Expressing his delightedness to meet with Bird in Beijing, Qian
said that since Bird's last visit to China, China has experienced
great changes and made remarkable progress as a result of reforms and
opening up.
</P>
<P>
However, with a large population and a poor foundation to start
with, China remains a developing country, he said, adding that
China will concentrate on expanding its economy.
</P>
<P>
He noted that in the international arena, China holds that all
countries should respect each another, not interfere in each
other's internal affairs and conduct mutually beneficial
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He praised the people of Antigua and Barbuda for their
achievements in national construction. He stressed that China will
continue to actively push forward friendly cooperation between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
Bird said that 12 years have passed since he first visited
China. He is impressed by the amazing and admirable development of
China. He said that China has always been a reliable friend of
other developing countries. He noted that China's support to his
country's effort to develop the economy in the past years has
greatly encouraged his people.
</P>
<P>
Qian noted that since its return to the motherland some 100
days ago, Hong Kong has maintained social stability and economic
prosperity. The international financial and business communities are
optimistic about Hong Kong's future.
</P>
<P>
He said that these facts have proved that the "one country, two
systems" principle is successful. He said that the successful
implementation of the principle in Hong Kong will have a
significant impact on China's great cause of reunification.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that China's reunification of China is an
inevitable trend and that the "one China" policy has been
understood by an overwhelming majority of countries.
</P>
<P>
Qian and Bird also exchanged views on regional and
international issues.
</P>
<P>
Before the meeting, Bird attended a banquet given at noon by Yu
Xiaosong, president of the China Council for the Promotion of
International Trade. He briefed Chinese entrepreneurs on tourism,
finance and free trade zones of his country. He invited Chinese
entrepreneurs to invest and launch cooperation projects in his
country.  
</P>
