<HEADLINE> Foreign Investors to Enjoy Half Tariffs in Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Victor
Chernomyrdin said today that foreign investors in Russia will
enjoy special treatment in being charged only half the normal
tariffs.
</P>
<P>
The Itar-Tass news agency reported that Chernomyrdin, speaking
at a regular meeting of foreign investors, said a presidential
decree to this effect has been drafted.
</P>
<P>
He said the decree aimed to make sure that accords signed
between the Russian Ministry of Economy and big foreign investors
can be carried out.
</P>
<P>
Since last December, there have been a lot of legal disputes
because of the elimination of some preferential terms for foreign
investors.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin said he was optimistic about the future of foreign
investment in Russia. Judging from the development of the Russian
economy in the past nine months, Russian could attract 20 billion
U.S. dollars in investments annually by the year of 2000, he said.
</P>
<P>
There has been direct foreign investment of four billion
U.S. dollars in Russia this year. So far, the overall foreign
investment in the country has surpassed 20 billion
U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
