<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Sells Two Government Lots </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Two government lots were sold
for a total of 8.5 billion HK dollars (1.09 billion U.S. dollars)
at a public auction held by the Lands Department this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The first lot, located in Tai Po with an area of 91,265
square meters, was sold to Wealth Team Development Limited for 5.6
billion HK dollars (717.95 million U.S. dollars), with bidding
opened at 3.5 billion HK dollars (448,72 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The developer has to complete a gross floor area of not less
than 64,900 square meters on or before December 31, 2002. The lot
is intended for private residential use, excluding service
apartments.
</P>
<P>
The second lot in Tuen Mun has an area of 16,587 square meters.
</P>
<P>
It was bought by Macfull Limited for 2.9 billion HK dollars
(371.79 million U.S. dollars), with bidding opened at 1.5 billion
HK dollars (192.31 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The developer has to complete a gross floor area of not less
than 62,000 square meters on or before December 31, 2002. The site
is intended for non-industrial use, excluding godown, petrol
filling station, hotel and service apartments. 
</P>
