<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao SAR Preparatory Committee Won't Be 2nd Power Center: Chinese Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 14 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese official on Hong
Kong and Macao affairs said here today that the Preparatory
Committee for the Establishment of the Macao Special
Administrative Region (SAR) will not become a second power center
in Macao.
</P>
<P>
Chen Ziying, deputy director of the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs
Office under the State Council of China, who arrived here Monday
on a five-day visit, told an audience of some 400 people that the
committee will be conducive to Macao's smooth transition.
</P>
<P>
"All the committee will do is only for the establishment of the
Macao SAR, which will come into being after China resumes exercise
of sovereignty over Macao on December 20, 1999," he stressed. "It
will never interfere in the Portuguese administration in Macao
that will last until December 19, 1999."
</P>
<P>
Chen said that he is confident the establishment of the
committee will have the active participation and support of Macao
residents and the full understanding and cooperation of the
Portuguese side.
</P>
<P>
The preparatory committee is widely expected to be set up early
next year. But details on the founding of the body, including the
number of committee members, the exact time of its founding, are
yet to be announced.
</P>
<P>
According to a decision of China's National People's Congress
(NPC), the preparatory committee will be composed of members from
the mainland and "no less than 50 percent of Macao members."
</P>
<P>
Chen explained that, based on the experience of the Hong Kong
SAR Preparatory Committee and the specific situation in Macao,
more than half of the committee members will be local Macao
residents, and they will be representatives of all walks of life
in Macao.
</P>
<P>
The preparatory committee will be responsible for matters
related to the establishment of the Macao SAR, including the ways
to form the first administration, the first legislative assembly
and the first judiciary organs, according to the NPC
decision. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
