<HEADLINE> Li Peng Meets Egyptian Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng said today that
the Communist Party of China (CPC) and the Chinese government
attach great importance to the growth of the friendly ties with
Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Li, also a Standing Committee member of the Political Bureau of
the CPC Central Committe, made the remark this afternoon in a
meeting with a delegation from the National Democratic Party (NDP)
of Egypt, led by the NDP deputy secretary-general and minister of
the Egyptian People's Assembly and Advisory Council, Kamal
El-Shazli.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of the CPC Central Committee, Li expressed welcome
to Shazli and his delegation, saying that the friendship between
the two peoples dates back to ancient times.
</P>
<P>
Since China and Egypt established diplomatic relations 41 years
ago, Li said, bilateral friendship and cooperation in various
areas such as politics, the economy and culture have developed
smoothly.
</P>
<P>
The two countries share identical or similar views on many
major international issues, and have always supported each other
and cooperated with each other closely in international affairs,
added Li.
</P>
<P>
Li said he is convinced that with concerted efforts, the
relations between the two parties and the two countries will be
furthered on the basis of the Four Principles guiding
party-to-party relations and the Five Principles of Peaceful
Co-Existence.
</P>
<P>
He said that Chinese government is ready to further economic
and trade relations with Egypt on the basis of equality and
mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that relevant departments of both
countries should decide on cooperative projects through
investigations and negotiations, according to the Premier.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that Chinese government highly appreciates
the important role played by the Egyptian government and
people in supporting the Palestinian people's just cause, advancing
the peace process in the Middle East, and enhancing unity and
cooperation among Arab states and African nations.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of Egyptian President Mubarak and the NDP, Shazli
congratulated the CPC on the successful convocation of its 15th
National Congress and the return of Hong Kong to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Shazli said that the Egyptian ruling Party and government have
a high opinion of China's achievements, appreciate the Chinese
government's and people's position on supporting Arab people's
just cause, and are willing to make further efforts to promote the
friendship and cooperation between the two parties and the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Head of the International Department of the CPC Central
Committee Dai Bingguo was present at the meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
