<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets With Antigua and Barbuda Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress Qiao Shi met with
Prime Minister Lester Bird of Antigua and Barbuda in the Great
Hall of the People today.
</P>
<P>
Extending welcome to Bird, Qiao said that Bird's visit will
further push forward the development of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that China always holds that all countries, big
or small, are equal. China maintains that relations between
countries should be based on the Five Principles of
Peaceful Coexistence.
</P>
<P>
He said that China opposes big countries bellying small ones
and strong countries bullying weak ones. He said that China
also holds that all countries should increase exchanges and
conduct economic cooperation on the basis of equality and mutual
benefit.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the belief that as the two countries deepen mutual
understanding, bilateral cooperative relations will continue to
develop.
</P>
<P>
Qiao expressed appreciation for Antigua and Barbuda's adherence
to the "one China" stand.
</P>
<P>
Bird said that the government of his country treasures its
friendly relations with China. The country established diplomatic
relations with China soon after winning independence. It has
always pursued the "one China" policy and will continue to do so
in the future, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that during his visit, satisfactory results have been
scored by enhancing mutual understanding and through extensive
discussions with Chinese hosts about the channel through which to
strengthen bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He also briefed Qiao on the efforts that his country and other
Caribbean countries have made to safeguard their sovereignty and
develop their economies.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said that China is concerned with and supports the
development of Caribbean countries. He noted that the
strengthening of the friendly cooperative relations between China
and these countries will contribute to world peace and development.
</P>
<P>
Qiao also asked Bird to convey his greetings to the heads of
the Parliament of Antigua and Barbuda. 
</P>
</TEXT>
