<HEADLINE> CPPCC Chairman Meets Prime Minister of Antigua and Barbuda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese leader said
here today that China is implementing its foreign policy in
conformity with the long-term interests of the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, chairman of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) National Committee, told visiting
Prime Minister Lester Bird of Antigua and Barbuda that the
independent foreign policy of peace pursued by his country is
"not an expedient measure."
</P>
<P>
It is in the interests of the people that China develops
friendly relations with all the countries in the world, including
Antigua and Barbuda, Li said.
</P>
<P>
Li noted that the 20th century has witnessed rapid
economic growth, scientific progress and great suffering caused by
war.
</P>
<P>
Based on the historic experiences, Li went on, "we have to
focus on seeking world peace and common development."
</P>
<P>
He added that the Chinese government regards economic
development and the improvement of the people's living standards
as its central tasks.
</P>
<P>
The CPPCC leader added that China attaches importance to its
cooperation with Antigua and Barbuda in bilateral sphere and in
international affairs.
</P>
<P>
China also admires Antigua and Barbuda's role in regional
affairs, Li said.
</P>
<P>
Bird told Li that he held fruitful talks with Chinese leaders.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China has always treated other countries equally,
adding that the relations between his country and China demostrate
that big and small nations can forge equal and friendly
relations and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister said his country is making effort to
eliminate poverty and strive for development. He added that
his country and China can conduct more economic and technological
cooperation toward this end.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister of the Caribbean island nation arrived here
Monday as guest of Chinese Premier Li Peng.  
</P>
