<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel
Ramos said here today that his country has avoided the recent
overheating currency crisis "pretty well," describing its economy
as "structurally sound."
</P>
<P>
Addressing the Sixth East Asia Economic Summit organized by the
World Economic Forum, Ramos said the political and economic
situation in his country now is normal.
</P>
<P>
