<HEADLINE> Israeli Ambassador Intervenes in Trial of Ex-Vichy Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Ambassador to France, Avi
Pazner, will tour Bordeaux to support Jewish groups during the
trial of former Vichy official Maurice Papon.
</P>
<P>
Pazner and Daniel Saada, a first secretary of the embassy, are
scheduled to meet representatives of Jewish groups on Wednesday,
said an Agence France-Presse (AFP) report.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, "reliable sources" were quoted as saying, will be
at the groups' support commission near the Palace of Justice of
Bordeaux where Papon is standing trial.
</P>
<P>
Papon was accused of crimes against humanity for his role in
the deportation of some 1,500 Jews from the Gironde Prefecture in
southwest France to Nazi death camps from 1942 to 1944.
</P>
<P>
At the time, he served as the secretary general of Gironde
under the Vichy collaboration regime.
</P>
<P>
Two days after the opening of his trial, Papon, 87, was
released from jail by the Assize Court of Bordeaux on health
reasons, triggering strong protests from Jewish and civil groups.
</P>
