<HEADLINE> Myanmar Introduces First Call Deposit Account </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The Asia Wealth Bank, a Myanmar
private bank, has initiated a call deposit account in its banking
business, becoming the first bank to introduce such service in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Chairman of the bank U Aik Htun said at a press conference
here today that the move was aimed at attracting more depositors
and reducing the circulation of cash, thus contributing to
bringing down the inflation rate and preventing instability of
commodity prices.
</P>
<P>
The Asia Wealth Bank is one of the 25 private banks in Myanmar,
which are allowed to engage in banking business after the country
reformed its financial management system to keep in line with the
market-oriented economy introduced in the late 1980s.
</P>
<P>
Since then, foreign banks have also been permitted to open
representative offices in Myanmar. Of the 48 foreign bank offices
approved, 44 have opened.  
