<DOCNO> XIE19971014.0167 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Steady on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Share prices rallied during
today's trading on the Singapore market but fell back later as the
benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index closed at 1878.25
points, up by 0.56 points from Monday's finish.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume shrank to 108.43 million units, valued
at 256.65 million Singapore dollars (about 166.66 million US
dollars). Advances overtook declines by 149 to 118, while 350
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NatSteel Elec was the most actively traded counter as it
registered a turnover of 11.9 million units. It was followed by
the Hong Kong Land which had 5.4 million shares traded. Local
compact disc maker Summit was next with 5.28 million shares
changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Uniphoenix led the gainers of the day as it rose by 40 cents to
finish at 7.6 Singapore dollars. The Development Bank of Singapore
(DBS) Foreign, the Oriental Holdings, Robinson, and the Singapore
Land gained 30 cents each to end at 16.1, 4.3, 7.35, and 6.55
Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Southern Bank Foreign was the biggest loser as
it declined by 97 cents to close at 1.37 Singapore dollars. Bukit
Sembawang fell by 70 cents to finish at 21.8 Singapore dollars,
while the NatSteel lost 30 cents to end at 3.62 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
