<HEADLINE> Chiese City Builds Large Flower Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Shenyang, capital of northeast
China's Liaoning province, on Monday put into operation a
24,000-square-meter flower base, the largest in north China.
</P>
<P>
With 1,000 transaction stands, the flower base, called the
China Northern Flower City, will provide sites for the production
and trade of flowers. It was built at a cost of nearly 100 million
yuan.
</P>
<P>
The lotus-shaped structure is called "green palace," with eight
scenic spots. An open-air market covers an area of 12,000 square
meters. A nearly 10,000-square-meter cultivation and plantation
garden has introduced advanced technology from the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning province plans to raise its flower production acreage
to 6,700 hectares by the year 2000, which would generate 2 billion
yuan a year. 
</P>
