<HEADLINE> Chinese President's US Visit to Boost Sino-US Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin's
forthcoming state visit to the United States will promote mutual
understanding and friendship between the two countries and their
peoples, and bring the bilateral relations to a new period of
development.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Shen Guofang today told a
press conference that President Jiang Zemin will pay a state visit
to the US from October 26 to November 2 at the invitation of US
President William Clinton.
</P>
<P>
Shen said that during the visit, President Jiang Zemin and
President Clinton will hold talks in Washington, having an
in-depth exchange of views on China-US relations, the current
international situation and major issues of mutual interset, and
jointly establish the guidelines governing bilateral relations
oriented towards the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
In addition to Washington, President Jiang will also visit New
York, Boston, Los Angeles, etc.
</P>
<P>
Shen said, "President Jiang's state visit to the US will
definitely promote mutual understanding and friendship between
China and the United States and between the two peoples, and bring
bilateral relations to a new period." 
</P>
</TEXT>
