<HEADLINE> China Eastern Airlines Takes Delivery of Two Boeing MD-90s </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- China Eastern Airlines
has received a shipment of two Boeing MD-90 jet aircraft.
</P>
<P>
The MD-90s are the first two of the nine that will be delivered
to the carrier. The planes are configured to accommodate 158
passengers in two-classes of service, and have a range of 3,860
kilometers.
</P>
<P>
The new airplanes are targeted for use in east China's Anhui
Province, one of the most heavily traveled regions in the country,
China Eastern said.
</P>
<P>
The first MD-82 delivered to China in 1983 is part of the China
Eastern fleet, which includes 13 MD-80s and six MD-11s.
</P>
<P>
China Eastern, founded in 1988, serves China on both
international and domestic routes from its base in Shanghai. It is
the first carrier in China's history to go public, with 35 percent
of its stock offered on the Hong Kong and New York stock markets.
</P>
<P>
</P>
