<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Over 30 People Die of Cholera in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, October 14 (Xinhua) -- About 30 people have died of
cholera in Homa Bay and Kisumu town, western Kenya, in the past
three days, according to a "Daily Nation" report today.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted Nyanza Provincial Commissioner Wilson
Chepkwony as sending out an emergency appeal to Kenyan Ministry
of Health to send more drugs and vehicles to help stem the spread
of cholera in the province.
</P>
<P>
Nyanza provincial medical officer Richard Otieno Muga
yesterday held a crisis meeting with senior medical officers in
the province and said that vital facilities had been arrived
there to help contain the disease.
</P>
<P>
Medical authorities of the province has warned that the
disease, which has so far killed more than 200 people in the
province in the past two months, is spreading fast in residential
and the suburbs of Kisumu town.
</P>
<P>
The crisis meeting decided to convert five municipal health
centers into cholera treatment camps and all eating places which
do not meet the public health standards would be closed.
</P>
<P>
The Kibuye open air market in the town may not be allowed to
operate if health standards are not improved by this Friday,
sources of the meeting disclosed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
