<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Missing Exam Papers Found </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwe Junior Certificate
(ZJC) and Ordinary (O) level examination papers which went
missing in Manicaland Province on Monday Last week were found in
Nyanga, east Zimbabwe this Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to Schools Examination Council Director Isaiah
Sibanda, the papers, which went missing from the carrier of a bus
on transit to Avilla Secondary School, were found by the police
in a toilet pit at the homestead of a suspect.
</P>
<P>
"The mathematics, English, science and Shona papers were still
intact and in their plastic envelopes. The rest of the question
papers have been burnt halfway or quarter way, but these, too,
have been accounted for," Sibanda said.
</P>
<P>
He said the possibility of a leakage had been ruled out by the
police but would continue to monitor the situation to ensure that
nothing had leaked.
</P>
<P>
"In view of the circumstances indicated, we intend to proceed
with the examinations as planned, albeit being vigilant that no
leakages have occurred," he said.
</P>
<P>
He added the suspect was being held by the police.
</P>
<P>
Acting Permanent Secretary of the Education, Sport and Culture
Ministry M. M'kumbuzi said people responsible for the mishap
would be disciplined. 
</P>
</TEXT>
