<HEADLINE> Yang Xia Lifts World Records To Take 54-kg Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Teenager Yang Xia lifted up
three world records to claim the women's 54-kg category title at
the Eighth National Games here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The 19-year-old strongwoman of Hunan province, snatched 100kgs
and jerked up 132.5 kgs for a total of 232.5kgs, all surpassing
the listed world marks in the event.
</P>
<P>
The previous snatch mark of 93.5 kgs and the two-lift total of
207.5 kgs was set by herself in the Asian Weightlifting
Championships in July this year where Liu Xiuhua set up the jerk
record of 115.5 kgs.
</P>
<P>
Yang Xia also broke the national jerk record of 130 kgs set up
by Chen Xiaomin at the previous National Games in Beijing four
years ago.
</P>
<P>
Nine of the 12 finalists surpassed all three world records in
the Eighth National Games.
</P>
<P>
Long Yuling of Hunan province took the silver medal after
snatching up a new world record of 102.5 kgs and jerked up 127.5
kgs for a total of 230 kgs.
</P>
<P>
The bronze medal went to Zhang Xixiang of Guangdong province
with a total of 225kgs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
