<HEADLINE> Chinese General Staff Chief Meets Belgian Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Fu Quanyou, chief of the
General Staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army, met today
with Belgian Defense Minister Jean-Paul Ponsle.
</P>
<P>
Ponsle and his party were welcomed by Fu, who recalled his
visit to Belgium in March.
</P>
<P>
Since the establishment of Sino-Belgian diplomatic relations in
1971, Fu said, bilateral relations have grown
continuously. Exchanges between the armed forces of the two
countries have been expanded through frequent exchange of
high-level visits, he added.
</P>
<P>
Ponsle's current visit will help strengthen mutual
understanding and promote friendly relations of cooperation
between the two nations and their armed forces, Fu said.
</P>
<P>
Expressing his gratitude for the warm reception by the Chinese,
Ponsle said he was satisfied with his trip and impressed by the
military performance by Chinese soldiers. 
</P>
