<HEADLINE> USAID Donates $8.5M Textbooks to Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The United States Agency for
International Development (USAID) has donated 8.5 million U.S.
Dollars textbooks for Uganda's primary schools, reported local
daily "The Monitor" today.
</P>
<P>
A total of about 2.1 million textbooks and teachers guidelines
worth about 8.5 million Dollars were donated by the USAID, said
the paper.
</P>
<P>
These books are to be distributed to over 8,500 primary
schools in accordance with the established enrollment figures
under the first and second instructional material procurement
cycles in 1995 and 1996, it disclosed.
</P>
<P>
Uganda started free primary education for four children from
each family early this year, aiming at increasing primary school
enrollment rate from 2.1 percent of the 3.98 million children of
6-12 years in the country last year to 81.6 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
