<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "Father of Hybrid Rice" Flexes Muscle in Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Leading agronomist
Yuan Longping, known as the "father of hybrid rice", has taken on
a new post to flex his muscle in market competition: chairman of a
joint venture company.
</P>
<P>
Hunan province held a trade fair in September, at which the
American Rice Tech-AG signed a contract with the province's Hybrid
Rice Research Center, where Yuan is working. The two sides agreed
to invest 10 million U.S. dollars to establish the Yuan Longping
Hybrid Rice International Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture will aim at spreading the use of hybrid rice
technologies, raising rice production efficiency and promoting
world grain growth. It will bring large, stable and lasting
returns to the partners, an official at the research center said.
</P>
<P>
The company will have sales of 67.8 million yuan this year,
including profits of 5.69 million yuan, according to feasibility
studies.
</P>
<P>
The company plans to plant hybrid rice on 3.3 million hectares
in China by 2000, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Some people expressed concern about losing an excellent
scientist, but Yuan said the joint venture would help expand the
use of hybrid rice to the rest of the world. By doing business he
will have more capital to support his research, Yuan said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
