<HEADLINE> East China Province Leads in Parks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The 23 national forest parks in
east China's Anhui province give it the most of any Chinese
province.
</P>
<P>
The total 120,000 hectares of woods, including 12 provincial
forest parks, attracted an annual average of four million tourists
in the past three years, 10 times that of 1994.
</P>
<P>
Many urban visitors from east China cities, including Shanghai,
joined the woods tour because of their proximity.
</P>
<P>
To boost tourism, the provincial government poured more
than 100 million yuan into park design and building roads.
</P>
<P>
A long-term development project for 30 parks is being
considered.
</P>
<P>
Tiantangzhai Park in the Dabie Mountains will soon have a
cableway, using equipment imported from Germany and
Sweden. 
</P>
</TEXT>
