<HEADLINE> 11th World Forestry Congress Opens in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The 11th World Forestry
Congress opened today in southern Turkey's resort town of Antalya
with the participation of 4,000 delegates from around 150
countries.
</P>
<P>
The theme of the congress is "Forestry for Sustainable
Development Towards the 21st Century."
</P>
<P>
A number of topics, including the forestry policies, rational
utilization of forestry resources, prevention of forest fire,
will be discussed during the conference, national radio and tv
stations reported.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the opening ceremony, Turkish Forestry Minister Ersin
Taranoglu was quoted as saying that this conference will be a new
step in fighting against the forestry enemies.
</P>
<P>
The session, jointly sponsored by Turkey and the United
Nations' Food and Agriculture Organization, will be this century's
last world forestry congress, which usually takes place every
six years.
</P>
<P>
The conference will be concluded on October 22. 
</P>
</TEXT>
