<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Face Shortage in Domestic Gas Supply in 2020 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Domestic supply of natural gas
is likely to be unable to meet demand in China in the year 2020, a
group of Chinese researchers predicted.
</P>
<P>
By 2020, the annual output of natural gas is expected to reach 58
to 85 billion cubic meters, while consumption will hit 88 to 105
billion cubic meters, according to the researchers' paper submitted
to the ongoing 15th World Petroleum Congress.
</P>
<P>
But in the short term, supply and demand of natural gas will be
basically balanced, with output estimated at 26 to 35 billion
cubic meters and consumption at 26 to 29 billion cubic meters in
2000, according to researchers with the China National Star
Petroleum Corporation.
</P>
<P>
To date, a total of 138 gas fields have been discovered in 21
sedimentary basins in China, with annual production standing at
20.13 billion cubic meters last year.
</P>
<P>
The researchers shared the view that potential increase of
natural gas use in the future will be concentrated in residential
and commercial sector that is expected to account for more than 30
percent and 50 percent of the national total in the years 2000 and
2020 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, they noted that natural gas will also play an
important role in the chemical industry, which will account for 26
percent and 23 percent of the nation's total gas consumption in
2000 and 2020 respectively.
</P>
<P>
To meet the future demand for natural gas, particularly beyond
the year 2020, they said, explorations and developments of
conventional natural gas should be accelerated.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, it is necessary for China to seek other sources of
natural gas, including increased imports, coalbed methane, tight
sandstone gas and deep gas, they said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
