<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NZ Sharemarket Rises to 10-Year High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
rallied today with the leading market indicator rising to a
10-year high, pushed up by gains in leading stocks.
</P>
<P>
However, the rally was not carried through to the second-line
stocks with smaller companies index falling.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended 21 points higher at 2613 with a turnover
 of 98 million NZ dollars (63 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Forty percent of the trading was in Fletcher Energy shares,
which surged 68 cents after obtaining positive evaluation in the
United States. The shares closed at 815 cents, but off its morning
high of 848 cents. Also higher were Telecom shares, rising 8 cents
to 816 cents; Air New Zealand, gaining 6 cents to 287 cents; and
Carter Holt Harvey, picking up 2 cents to 360 cents.
</P>
<P>
But Brierley Investment remained unchanged at 137 cents and
Lion Nathan lost 2 cents to 397 cents.
</P>
<P>
Overall, rises outnumbered falls by 57 to 43.  
</P>
</TEXT>
