<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Venezuela, China to Cooperate in Emulsified Oil Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Venezuela and China will
jointly exploit and produce emulsified oil for mutual benefit,
said Carlos Borregales, president and chief executive of
Venezuela's Orinoco Bitumen Company, at the 15th World Petroleum
Congress (WPC) Monday.
</P>
<P>
Venezuela has 40 billion tons of bitumen reserves, while China
has worked out a plan for energy development. The Orinoco bitumen,
a new type of fuel, has found favor with power stations, he said.
</P>
<P>
Orinoco emulsified oil -- a term invented by Venezuela -- is a
mixture of bitumen, water and some chemicals, and has become a
preferred fuel for power plants and other industrial uses.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, China and Venezuela signed an agreement for 320
million U.S. dollars to cooperate on the production of emulsified
oil, now widely used in Shangdong province and Shanghai
municipality in east China.
</P>
<P>
Borregales said Venezuela-China cooperation has been effective
so far and offers encouraging possibilities.
</P>
<P>
Venezuela is the world's largest bitumen producer and has set a
goal of 20 million tons annually of emulsified oil. It had 4.17
million tons of exports last year and expects 4.7 million this
year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
