<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Importance of Environmental Protection Stressed at WPC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Participants to the ongoing
15th World Petroleum Congress have reached consensus that it is
vital for the industry to make more efforts to tackle
environmental issues.
</P>
<P>
They have held shared concern about maintaining the momentum of
global economic growth while promoting environmental protection
worldwide, Paul Tempest, director general of the congress, said at
a press conference here this morning.
</P>
<P>
But as conditions differ from country to country, it is
impossible to impose a single global standard on the issue and
countries have to deal with it in line with their own conditions,
Tempest said.
</P>
<P>
In fact, Tempest said, stepping up environmental protection
provides immense opportunity for the world oil and gas industry as
it develops into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he added, participants have been fully aware of the
process of globalization and called for acceleration in
technological transfer on the global market.
</P>
<P>
World economic growth has been dependent on supply of oil and
gas, and countries need to increase cooperation in the field,
Tempest said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
