<HEADLINE> Olympic Champin Le Fails to Make 200m Freestyle Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Olympic champion Le Jingyi
surprisingly failed to make the finals of the women's 200-meter
freestyle here on Tuesday at the Eighth National Games.
</P>
<P>
Le who won the 100m freestyle with the year's best time of
54.10 seconds on Monday, clocked 2 minutes 1.64 seconds in the
heats this morning.
</P>
<P>
Chen Yan of Liaoning province, who broke the world record in
the women's 400m individual medley on Monday, timed first in
1:59.60 to pace other seven swimmers for the finals, including
Le's four teammates from Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Le, the world record holder in the 50m and 100m freestyles,
swam the fastest in the first 50 meters but was overtaken by her
opponents in the later stage.
</P>
<P>
Coach Zhou Ming said "I was a little bit surprised for her
failure to make the finals after she finished the distance in such
a timing."
</P>
<P>
"However, the situation also suggested that China enjoyes a
maturing young generation in the discipline," Zhou explained.
</P>
</TEXT>
