<HEADLINE> Kafelnikov Wins Lyon Tennis Opener </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Second-seeded Yevgeny Kafelnikov
of Russia easily won the opener of the 750,000 U.S. dollars Lyon
Grand Prix tennis tournament on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Russian used just over a hour to defeat New Zealand's Brett
Stevens 6-1, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
In other matches, Tommy Haas of Germany spent less than one
hour to beat Albert Portas of Spain 6-1, 6-3 and Richey Reneberg
of the United States overwhelmed Filip Dewulf of Belgium, 7-6
(7-5), 5-7, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Top seeded Pat Rafter of Australia will play its opening match
with French wild card Arnaud Clement on Tuesday. 
</P>
