<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 18 more Dengue Cases Reported in New Delhi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The dengue virus is steadily
expanding in the Indian capital of New Delhi with 18 more cases of
the disease reported on Monday, the local press said today.
</P>
<P>
The total number of dengue cases in various hospitals in the
capital has risen to 181. Two patients, including a nine-month-old
girl, have already died due to the deadly virus.
</P>
<P>
Despite the local authorities' assurances that all steps are
being taken to keep the aedes mosquitoes, which transmit the
dengue virus, at bay, people in various localities still complain
about inadequate measures.
</P>
<P>
Doctors here have warned people against taking fever cases
lightly because early detection of dengue makes its treatment
easier.
</P>
<P>
They explained that if there is any delay in taking the patient
to the doctor, dangerous internal bleeding may set in.
</P>
<P>
An epidemic of dengue fever here last year claimed hundreds of
lives with nearly 10,000 people hospitalized.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
