<HEADLINE> Mercosur Education Seminar Opens in Chile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, October 13 (Xinhua) -- A seminar named "Education
Statistics of Mercosur", opened here today, which aims to promote
exchange of experiences in education reforms among member
countries of South American Common Market (Mercosur).
</P>
<P>
"Since we have three million students, while Brazil have 30
million students, ... the exchange of experiences is going to be
very rich, for it will help us innovate and improve our education
techniques", Chilean Education Minister, Jose Pablo Arellano, said
in his opening speech.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed that Mercosur goes beyond an economic
integration, which is to include education and cultural topics.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, Arellano added, it is necessary that all member
countries have a common statistical and background base.
</P>
<P>
The seminar also intends to present the systems of statistical
taxonomic indicators on education, and to facilitate the adoption
of agreements to implement a common education statistical basis
for the five member countries of Mercosur.
</P>
<P>
Experts in the production and distribution of education
statistics in Argentina, Paraguay, Uruguay and Chile attended the
meeting. 
</P>
