<HEADLINE> DPRK Newspaper Refutes `North Korean Threat' </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Rodong Sinmun, the official
newspaper of the Worker's Party in Korea, today carried a
commentary refuting the U.S. charge of a so-called "North Korean
threat."
</P>
<P>
The commentary pointed out that "the most dangerous threat to
existence is not us but the United States," adding that "we never
threatened the U.S., but the U.S. is threating us."
</P>
<P>
The commentary came in response to the recent U.S. report on
national security strategy, which accused the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK) as being a dangerous threat to existence
and has a wild ambition to challenge the U.S. military presence.
</P>
<P>
The commentary said the accusation confounds black and white,
attempting to sabotage and strangle the socialism of the DPRK.
</P>
<P>
"So long as the U.S. continues to adopt an invading and hostile
policy towards the DPRK, so long as the U.S. continues to increase
its military presence in South Korea and other neighboring
regions, the DPRK has no alternative but to strengthen its
self-defense forces," said the commentary. 
