<HEADLINE> Caldera, Clinton Support Hemispheric Free Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Venezuelan President Rafael
Caldera and U.S. President Bill Clinton today reiterated their
commitment to continuing efforts to create a free trade
zone in the Americas by 2005.
</P>
<P>
Both presidents vowed to support the extensive free trade
negotiations that will start in 1998 at the western hemisphere
summit in Santiago, Chile.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Washington and Caracas also agreed to
increase Venezuelan oil exports to the United States, already the
largest foreign oil supplier to the U.S.
</P>
