<DOCNO> XIE19971014.0259 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Restores Trade Privileges for Laotian Textiles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) has
resumed its trade privileges for Laotian textile products,
according to a report from Vientiane.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting in the Laotian capital on Monday, Michel
Caillouet, head of the European Commission mission in Laos,
officially told Laotian Minister of Commerce Sompradith Vorasan of
the EU decision to restore the Generalized System of Preferences
(GSP) for Laotian textiles and Laos can now again enjoy reduced
tariff advantages for its textile exports to EU markets.
</P>
<P>
Laos's GSP privileges were withdrawn in 1995 after the EU
accused the country of violating the GSP rules of origin by using
excessive amounts of raw materials from other countries.
</P>
<P>
Last month the EU eased restriction by allowing Laotian
producers to use more raw materials from ASEAN member states.
</P>
<P>
Caillouet said the decision would encourage trade flows between
the EU and Laos and will promote investment in the country's
textile industry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
