<HEADLINE> Clinton to Visit Brazilian Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, October 13 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill
Clinton will visit Brazilian Congress during his two-day stay in
the country, Speaker Antonio Carlos Magalhaes said today.
</P>
<P>
The diplomatic crisis "is over," Magalhaes said, adding Brazil
was able to change the whole schedule of Clinton's visit.
</P>
<P>
Last Saturday Magalhaes threatened to impede Clinton's visit to
the Congress.
</P>
<P>
Magalhaes said that there will be no restrictions to the
number of Brazilian legislators to attend the reception
offered to Clinton, and that this event will be reported
by local press.
</P>
<P>
He added that U.S. government officials have accepted all the
changes they proposed to the original plans of Clinton's visit to
the congress.
</P>
<P>
Clinton was also to meet with the heads of both houses of
Congress Tuesday, before boarding a plane for Sao Paulo. He is
scheduled to fly to Rio de Janeiro Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Clinton arrived here tonight from Venezuela. He will later
continue on to Argentina, the last leg of his week-long South
American tour. 
</P>
</TEXT>
