<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Puts in Huge Investment in Oil and Gas Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan has invested Two
billion US dollars this year in the petroleum sector and it is
still witnessing substantial investment in both upstream and
downstream sectors of the petroleum industry, said a senior
Pakistan oil official.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the ministerial panel of the ongoing 15th World
Petroleum Congress (WPC), Chaudhry Nisar Ali Khan, minister of
petroleum and natural resources, said that Pakistan was the fastest
growing energy market in the world, rising by 13.6 percent last year.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the increase in exploration activities through which
some 30 new exploration concession agreements are being signed this
year, Pakistan is also seeing major investment in the downstream
sector with the start of work on a 900 million US dollars refinery
and substantial investment in the oil and gas pipeline network in
the country.
</P>
<P>
The official noted that Pakistan's biggest upcoming project is
the 2 billion US dollar transnational gas pipeline project from
Turkmenistan which has been recently signed between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
With imported gas, Pakistan will be able to meet gas demand
shortfall and also to achieve economically beneficial and
environmentally preferred replacement of oil by gas in power and
industrial sectors, the official said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
