<HEADLINE> German Reinsurance Giant Opens New Offices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Munich Reinsurance Company, the
world's professional reinsurance giant, has just opened two
offices in China to anticipate the further dynamic growth of
China's insurance industry, "China Daily" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of Beijing and Shanghai offices was an
important investment for the future and visible evidence of Munich
Re's increased commitment to China, said Hans-Jurgen Schinzler,
the company's chairman.
</P>
<P>
After conducting reinsurance business in China for 25 years, it
has developed various non-life insurance projects, focusing on
engineering, marine and satellite launching.
</P>
<P>
China's fast economic growth brings about a large number of key
technical projects, offering great potential for the engineering
reinsurance market.
</P>
<P>
The soaring foreign trade of China and the commercial launching
of satellites also provides chances for marine and satellite
reinsurance.
</P>
<P>
The company is negotiating with Chinese insurers, in a hope to
provide reinsurance services for China's massive Three Gorges
projects. 
</P>
