<HEADLINE> South Koreans Win at World Cup Speed Skating </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Fourth-ranked Lee Jun-Hwan of
South Korea companied with his top-ranked compatriot Chun
Lee-Kyung to snatch the men's and women's crown at the three-day
World Cup short track speed skating tournament in Lake Placid on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Lee won the men's 1,500-meter race in two minutes 25.63
seconds, six-hundredths of a second ahead of his top-ranked
compatriot Kim Dong-Sung, taking the men's crown with 10
points. Kim was second with eight.
</P>
<P>
South Korea's Chae Ji-Hoon was third in 2:25.91. China's Li
Jiajun took fourth in 2:26.04.
</P>
<P>
Chun topped the women's overall standings with 10 points and
Kim Yun-mi finished second with eight points. Kim took Monday's
women's 1,500m in 2:34.13 with Chun second in 2:35.27.
</P>
<P>
South Korea also swept the men's 5,000m and women's 3,000m
relays.
</P>
<P>
The World Cup circuit continues with the next event in
Groningen, Netherlands. 
