</P>
<P>
ATHENS -- An earthquake measuring 5.5 on the richter scale
shocked the Greek capital Monday afternoon, but no damages have
been reported.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake occurred at 4:40 p.m. local time with the
epicenter being in the seabed 250 kilometers southwest of Athens,
about 100 kilometers south of Kalamata in southern Pelopponese.
the Athens Seismological Institute and the Geophysics Laboratory
of the Aristotelian University of Thessaloniki said
Monday. (BC-Greece-Earthquake)
</P>
