<HEADLINE> Brazil, US to Sign Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Brazil and the United States
will sign a series of agreements during U.S. President Bill
Clinton's visit, the Foreign Ministry said today.
</P>
<P>
The agreements will cover wide-ranging areas such as education,
space cooperation, judiciary and criminal assistance, and the
peaceful use of nuclear energy.
</P>
<P>
Clinton is scheduled to arrive here tonight from Venezuela
where he started his one-week South American tour Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Clinton will stay in Brazil until Wednesday and plans to visit
Sao Paulo and Rio de Janeiro in addition of Brasilia. He will also
visit Brazilian parliament.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Clinton will have private meetings with
Brazilian President Fernando Henrique Cardoso. Their talks will
cover issues of common interest, bilateral trade problems, the
creation of a free trade zone in the Americas and reforms of the
United Nations.
</P>
<P>
Clinton's South American tour will also include Argentina.
</P>
