<HEADLINE> Myanmar Sets Free Thai Fishermen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Some 29 Thais charged with
illegal fishing in Myanmar waters have been released, according to
the Thai Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The crewmen, arrested in July and August, had been sentenced to
one and a half years in prison for violating Myanmar's fisheries
law.
</P>
<P>
They have been granted a pardon and will return home next
Tuesday, the ministry was quoted today by the local press as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, four Thai trawlers were seized by the Myanmar Navy
off Surin Island in the Andaman Sea on Saturday allegedly for
violating Myanmar's territorial waters.  
