<BODY>
<HEADLINE> British Jet Car Breaks Sound Barrier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 13 (Xinhua) -- A British car powered by
jet engines broke the sound barrier twice on land in Nevada on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
But the speed would not be recognized as a world record as it
took the driver Andy Green of Britain 61 minutes, not within 60
minutes as required by international racing rules, to drive the
British Thrust SuperSonic Car twice in a Nevada desert.
</P>
<P>
The speed for the first run was 1,222 kilometers per hour (kph)
while the second 1,216 kph. The speed of sound in the desert at
that time is 1,216 kph.
</P>
<P>
Team leader Richard Noble said his team was considering trying
again on Tuesday, the 50th anniversary of the first supersonic
airplane flight, by Chuck Yeager of the United States.
</P>
<P>
The Thrust SuperSonic Car set a world land speed record of
1,142 kph on September 25.
</P>
<P>
The car is powered by two Rolls-Royce jet engines from a
Phantom fighter aircraft. 
</P>
</TEXT>
