<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Williams Shines at European Indoors Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Young American Venus Williams
easily defeated Romania's Ruxandra Dragomir in the opening round of
the European indoor tennis championships in Zurich on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The 17-year-old American used 57 minutes to beat her 16th
ranked opponent 6-0, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Williams, ranked 26 in the world, lost to Swiss world number
one Martina Hingis in the finals of the U.S. Open tennis earlier
this year.
</P>
<P>
Sixth seed Anke Huber of Germany avenged a first round straight
set loss to Mary Joe Fernandez of the United States in Filderstadt
by downing the American 7-5, 6-0.
</P>
<P>
Among other matches, Anne-Gaelle Sidot of France edged
Slovakia's Karina Habsudova 6-2, 7-6 (7-3) and her compatriot
Nathalie Tauziat ousted Kimberly Po of the United States 6-3, 6-7
(5-7), 7-5. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
