<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Philippine Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Philippine newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Business World
</P>
<P>
-- Reflecting the erosion of the value of the peso against the
U.S. dollar, the national government incurred a budget deficit for
the first time this year.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine Star
</P>
<P>
-- Former President Corazon Aquino authorized the participation
of retired Gen. Jose Almonte in Operation Big Bird, the aborted
top-secret operation to recover the alleged hidden wealth of the
Marcos family in Swiss banks.
</P>
<P>
Manila Bulletin
</P>
<P>
-- The Senate ratified Monday two bicameral conference reports,
one creating child and family courts in at least 23 major cities
and the other, repealing the controversial anti-squatting law
which made squatting a crime in the past 22 years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
