<HEADLINE> South American Steel Distributors to Meet in Sao Paulo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Steel distributors
from South American Common Market (Mercosur) will meet next
thursday in Sao Paulo, to evaluate the growth of imports from
this trade bloc.
</P>
<P>
participants in the meeting will discuss mechanisms for the
strategic defense of mercosur, which is formed by Brasil,
Argentina, Paraguay and Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
Brasil should contribute with 82 percent of steel supplies in
Mercosur, due to its expected production of more than 26 million
tons this year.
</P>
<P>
Mercosur'S total steel production this year is estimated in 32
million tons.
</P>
<P>
Brasil is one of the main export markets for steel producers in
Argentina and Chile, which are the second and third most important
steel producers in south America, respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
