<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Four British Fans Get Suspended Sentences </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Four British soccer fans were
given suspended sentences by a Rome court on Monday for clashes
with police at Saturday's vital World Cup qualifier between Itlay
and England in the Olympic Stadium.
</P>
<P>
Three of the four got the sentences for attacking a police
officer which left the officer with head and abdomen injuries.
Another one was given the same sentence for "provoking police" in
a separate incident.
</P>
<P>
The fans' lawyer said it was a light punishment because they
were foreingers who would not create more problems and their
motives were just soccer match instead of something serious.
</P>
<P>
All the four admitted they were drunk. 
</P>
</TEXT>
