<DOCNO> XIE19971014.0301 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-13 21:45 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 9 Jordanians Released by Israel Back Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Nine more Jordanians released
from Israeli jails were flown here today on board a Royal
Jordanian helicopter, according to Radio Jordan.
</P>
<P>
The nine were set free by Israel as part of a deal with Jordan
in which Israel would have to release up to 70 Palestinians and
Jordanians from its prisons in exchange for its secret agents held
by Jordan in a bungled assassination attempt.
</P>
<P>
Radio Jordan said other Jordanians remaining in Israeli jails
are expected to be set free soon.
</P>
<P>
Last week, Israel freed spiritual leader and founder of the
Islamic Resistance Movement Hamas Sheikh Ahmed Yassin and 20 other
Palestinian and Jordanian prisoners.
</P>
<P>
Jordan released the two agents of Israel's intelligence service
Mossad arrested after they failed to kill Hamas political chief
Khaled Mashaal in Jordan's capital Amman September 25.
</P>
<P>
The swap of prisoners put an end to an offbeat episode between
Israel and its closest Arab friend Jordan, which was outraged by
Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's blunt action on its soil.
</P>
<P>
Jordan signed peace with Israel in 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
