<DOCNO> XIE19971014.0302 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-13 21:48 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Assad Calls for Active European Role in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Syrian President Hafez
al-Assad today called for more active role of European countries
in reactivating the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
He made the call when he met and had talks this afternoon with
Swedish Foreign Minister Lena Hjelm-Wallen who is on a three-day
official visit to Syria, according to the Damascus TV tonight.
</P>
<P>
Assad said Syria supports the peace process and he blamed
Israel for the deadlock of the peace march and for the tensions
escalating in the region.
</P>
<P>
The Swedish Minister, who arrived in Damascus last evening
called earlier today all parties in the region to try to make
further effort to save the peace process.
</P>
<P>
The Swedish Minister, after having talks with her Syrian
counterpart Farouq Sharaa today, told newsmen that being a member
of the European Union and the U.N. Security Council, Sweden is
seeking more facts about the situation and developments in the
region. This will help Sweden do something through the U.N. and the
EU, she said, adding that she wishes the EU will have greater
presence in seeking for a resolution of this conflict. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
