<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bus Accident Kills 20 in Quebec </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Twenty people were killed when a
bus with 30 aboard plunged into a ravine in the Canadian province
of Quebec, said reports today.
</P>
<P>
Survivors were taken to a nearby hospital.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred at around 2 p.m. on Highway 138, about
100 kilometers northeast of Quebec city.
</P>
<P>
It happened at the bottom of a steep hill heading into a hard
right curve, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Road conditions are reported to be dry and weather sunny.
</P>
<P>
The reports didn't mention what caused the fatal incident.
</P>
</TEXT>
