<DOCNO> XIE19971014.0304 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Edges Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, October 13 (Xinhua) -- New York stocks posted slim
gains today as the first full week of third-quarter profit reports
began on an upbeat note.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average rose just 27.01 points to
8,072.22 after a slow and steady retreat from an opening 70-point
jump.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock measures were mostly higher, with the Russell
2000 index of smaller companies managing a tiny gain in the final
minutes to close at a record high for the third straight session.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by an 8-to-7 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, where NYSE volume totaled just 351.20
million shares.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 1.12 to 968.10, and
the NYSE composite index rose 0.55 to 507.40.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index rose 3.08 at 1,742.11 after
retreating from an early foray into record territory.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 rose 0.18 to 465.21, but the American Stock
Exchange composite index, which is dominated by smaller companies,
fell 0.80 to 716.57. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
